14 WHEREAS, Mr. Abdul-Wahab's adept management has transformed NAFCO into a
15 financially self-sustaining entity, achieving profitability and reducing reliance on external
16 funding sources; and
17 WHEREAS, his initiatives have expanded NAFCO's operational reach throughout the
18 country, effectively mitigating post-harvest losses and optimizing agricultural resources; and
19 WHEREAS, Mr. Hanan Abdul-Wahab's exemplary achievements underscore his unwavering
20 commitment to excellence and innovation in advancing food security and economic
21 resilience in Ghana, setting a benchmark for sustainable agricultural practices and impactful
22 public service; and
23 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
24 remarkable and distinguished individual be appropriately recognized.
25 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
26 the members of this body recognize and commend Mr. Hanan Abdul-Wahab for his efficient,
27 effective, unselfish, and dedicated public service to Ghana and extend the most sincere best
28 wishes for continued health and happiness.
29 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
30 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Mr.
31 Hanan Abdul-Wahab.
